dct_description_sm: Relief shown by hachures, spot heights, and verbal descriptions. Routes and dates of expedition are shown. Includes lithograph illustration of landscape and inhabitants. From: The Journal of the Royal Geographical Society of London. Vol. 7, (1837), pp. 102-13; held in Firestone Library. Call number: G7 .J687 v.7 1837 Beldan Beni Shah, population 20 hamlets, is located.
dct_publisher_sm: London: published for the Journal of the Royal Geographical Society by John Murray, 1837.
